Following is the text of the U.S.
steel report from the Commerce Department:  The U.S. Census Bureau announced today that preliminary March
steel imports were $2.5 billion (2.2 million metric tons).  This
was an increase of $0.7 billion (0.6 million metric tons) from
the preliminary February totals of $1.8 bil  The March change in steel imports based on metric tonnage
reflected an increase primarily in blooms, billets, and slabs.
Increases occurred primarily with Mexico and  Canada .  The year to date final statistics through February 2011 showed
steel imports of 3.6 million metric tons compared with 2.9
million metric tons through February 2010. The largest commodity
increases occurred primarily in oil country go  Notes:  The data in this report are preliminary and subject to
revisions.  Analysis of recent months for steel product imports indicates
the value of preliminary data should equal about 96 percent of
the final value reported in the regular monthly trade statistics
report.  Preliminary data reported for indi  SOURCE: U.S. Commerce Department      http://www.bea.gov   To contact the reporter on this story:
